    <text>
        <body><div type="bibliography">
                
                <p><bibl>Morelli in <ptr target="#SECir"/>, <citedRange>232</citedRange> (no image)</bibl>; 
                    <bibl><ptr target="#IGCyr"/> <citedRange>103410</citedRange></bibl>.
                    Cf. <bibl><ptr target="#parisipresicce2007a"/>, p. <citedRange>498</citedRange></bibl>;
                    <bibl><ptr target="#rosamilia2023"/>, p. <citedRange>85</citedRange>, and footnote 71</bibl>.</p>
              </div><div type="edition" xml:lang="grc" xml:space="preserve">
                
                <div type="textpart" subtype="side" n="a"><ab>
                    <lb n="1"/><persName type="divine" ref="#Curete"><name nymRef="#Κωρής">Κωρ<unclear>ὴ</unclear><supplied reason="lost">ς</supplied></name> 
                        <placeName type="ethnic" nymRef="#Κρητικός"><supplied reason="lost">Κρη</supplied><unclear>τ</unclear>ικός</placeName></persName>
                </ab>
                </div>
                <div type="textpart" subtype="side" n="b"><ab>
                    <lb n="1"/><persName type="attested" key=""><name nymRef="#Χαρτάδας">Χαρτάδα</name></persName>
                </ab>
                </div>
                <div type="textpart" subtype="side" n="c">
                    <ab>
                        <lb n="1"/><persName type="attested" key=""><name nymRef="#Χαρτάδας"><expan><abbr>Χαρτά</abbr><ex>δα</ex></expan></name></persName>
                    </ab>
                </div>
                </div><div type="apparatus" xml:space="preserve">
            
                <p><app loc="a.1">
                    <lem>Κωρ<unclear>ὴ</unclear><supplied reason="lost">ς Κρη</supplied><unclear>τ</unclear>ικός</lem>
                    <rdg resp="#SECir">Κωρήτω</rdg>
                </app>
                </p>
               </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="fr">
            <p>Courète Crétois. <supplied reason="subaudible">J'appartiens à</supplied> Khartadas fils de Khartadas (?).</p>
            </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="en">
            <p>Cretan Curete. <supplied reason="subaudible">I belong to</supplied> Chartadas son of Chartadas (?).</p>
            </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="it">
            <p>Curete Cretese. <supplied reason="subaudible">Appartengo a</supplied> Chartadas figlio di Chartadas (?).</p>
            </div><div type="commentary">
                
                <p>Morelli's side a) = IGCyr side c); Morelli's side b) = IGCyr side b) ; Morelli's side c) = IGCyr side a)</p>
                <p>The surface is in very bad condition and nothing was read by C. Dobias-Lalou on the lateral faces, so that we are not able to indicate which one is on the right and which one is on the left.
                    Morelli's readings might correspond to an owner's mark, consisting either of a man's name (side b) with homonymous father's name (side c), as in translations above,
                    or of a name written twice and abbreviated on side c; in the latter case the meaning would be  <supplied reason="subaudible">I belong to</supplied> Chartadas; <supplied reason="subaudible">I belong 
                        to</supplied> <expan><abbr>Charta</abbr><ex>das</ex></expan>. <bibl><ptr target="#rosamilia2023"/></bibl> rightly points out that god's name and owner's name inscribed on the same 
                    altar are known only outside the city-walls (for instance at Ain Hofra or alongside the road to Balagrai).</p>
                <p>Morelli's reading for side a), <foreign xml:lang="grc">Κωρήτω</foreign>, is not acceptable on grammatical grounds.</p>
                <p>The mention <foreign xml:lang="grc">Κρητικός</foreign> is also attested in <ref type="inscription" source="#IGCyr2">IGCyr019600</ref>.</p>
            </div></body>
    </text>
